    "date": "2019-08-07T16:33:25Z",
    "text": "Mens Rea Reform Act of 2017 This bill establishes a default mens rea (i.e., guilty mind) requirement for federal criminal statutory and regulatory offenses that lack a state of mind requirement.\n\nThe government must generally prove that a defendant acted willfully with respect to each element of the offense that lacks a specific state of mind requirement."
